OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1784135918
OL,3,CTeenagers to face overnight social
OL,4,Cmedia curfew and infinite scrolling
OL,5,Cshut-down
OL,7,FColette Collins-Walsh, from the
OL,8,F5Rights Foundation ` a non-
OL,9,Fgovernmental organisation that
OL,10,Fcampaigns for online safety, said:
OL,11,F"Social media bans and curfews only
OL,12,Fmanage exposure to risk. They do
OL,13,Fnothing to incentivise change in a
OL,14,Ftech industry built on capturing
OL,15,Fchildren's attention.
OL,26,@sD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/17
